1.speaker: LADY
1.character: ご注文　お決まりですか？
1.definition: Are you ready to order? A polar bear?!

2.speaker: KIRINO
2.character: そ…　それじゃ 自己紹介から始めましょうか
2.definition: H-How about we start with introductions?

5.speaker: KIRINO
5.character: 動物園の飼育員をやっています
5.definition: I'm a zoo keeper. Nice to meet you.

7.speaker: HANDA
7.character: は…　は…　半田です！

8.speaker: HANDA
8.character: 本日は　このように 晴れがましい合コンに　お…　お招きいただき
8.definition: I-I humbly t-thank you f-for i-inviting me to this f-formal group blind date today.

9.speaker: HANDA
9.character: ふつつか者ではありますが
9.definition: I am quite inexperienced in this venture,

10.character: 以後　よろしく お見知りおきください
10.definition: but I'm pleased to make your acquaintance.

12.speaker: KIRINO
12.character: そこまで丁寧な 自己紹介じゃなくて大丈夫です
12.definition: Your introduction doesn't have to be that formal.

13.speaker: HANDA
13.character: けど　初対面だから
13.definition: But this is the first time I'm meeting them.

15.speaker: KIRINO
15.character: 合コンって　そういう感じのものじゃないんで
15.definition: Group blind dates aren't that formal.

16.speaker: HANDA
16.character: 続きまして 私と同じ職場に勤める
16.definition: In addition, please allow me to introduce you to Panda,

17.character: パンダくんを紹介します！

18.speaker: KIRINO
18.character: だから　かたいって…

19.speaker: KIRINO
19.character: すみません パンダ　連れてきちゃって
19.definition: I'm sorry, we brought a panda.

21.speaker: GIRLS
21.definition: So cute! They don't seem to mind Panda being here. And then we have...

22.speaker: POLAR BEAR
22.character: シロクマです ふだんは　カフェやってます
22.definition: I'm Polar Bear. I run a café.

25.speaker: GIRL
25.definition: I want to go! What's it called?

26.speaker: POLAR BEAR
26.definition: Polar Bear's Café. So straight to the point.

27.speaker: GIRL
27.character: あの　もしかして 雑誌とかに載ってないですか？
27.definition: By any chance, was it featured in any magazines?

29.speaker: GIRL
29.character: すごい！　見たことある
29.definition: Wow! I've totally seen it before!

30.speaker: GIRL
30.character: 今度　行ってもいいですか？
30.definition: Is it okay if we stop by sometime?

33.speaker: POLAR BEAR
33.character: 趣味は　アザラシの捕獲

35.speaker: GIRL
35.character: 今度連れてってください
35.definition: Can you take us with you next time?

36.speaker: KIRINO
36.definition: I don't think that's a good idea.

37.speaker: GIRL
37.character: じゃあ　女子 いきますね

39.speaker: KIRINO
39.character: 先輩　ヒロミちゃん

44.speaker: HANDA
44.character: わかってるよ　大丈夫 聞こえるから
44.definition: I know, I can hear them just fine. Go ahead with your order. Let's start off with draft beers.

46.speaker: PANDA
46.definition: Let's start off with bamboo. Bamboo?

47.character: ちょっと 置いてないんですが…
47.definition: I'm sorry, we don't carry that...

48.speaker: PANDA
48.character: え～っ　じゃあ　笹
48.definition: Really? Then how about bamboo grass?

49.speaker: LADY
49.character: 笹も　ないんですが…

50.speaker: PANDA
50.character: じゃあ　みんな　どうしてるの？
50.definition: Then what do you usually order?

54.speaker: POLAR BEAR
54.character: とりあえず　アザラシ

56.speaker: POLAR BEAR
56.definition: Can I bring some from home?

57.speaker: KIRINO
57.definition: No. Let's just start with six draft beers and one juice.

59.speaker: GIRL
59.character: そうよね　パンダっていったら やっぱり竹よね
59.definition: I guess that makes sense, he is a panda after all.

60.speaker: GIRL
60.character: 食べてるとこ　見てみたい
60.definition: I totally want to see him eat it.

61.speaker: GIRL
61.definition: That'd be so cute! You should totally eat bamboo!

62.speaker: KIRINO
62.character: 何なんだ？　この合コン…
62.definition: What kind of group blind date is this?

63.speaker: PENGUIN
63.character: いや　僕はね　合コンに行きたいって言ってるわけじゃないんだよ
63.definition: I'm not saying that I want to go to the group blind date.

65.speaker: PENGUIN
65.character: ただね　僕がずっとパンダくんの話を聞いていたわけだからさ
65.definition: It's just I was the one listening to Panda's story that whole time,

66.speaker: PENGUIN
66.character: 誘うなら　僕を誘うでしょ？
66.definition: so wouldn't it be natural for him to ask me?

67.speaker: PENGUIN
67.character: 僕にはペン子さんとい ペンギンがいるわけだから
67.definition: I have a penguin named Penko so I don't really want to go, but perhaps to study social activities...

69.speaker: PENGUIN
69.character: だから行きたくないよ
69.definition: I just told you that I didn't want to go.

70.speaker: PENGUIN
70.character: 笹子さんも　笹子さんでしょ
70.definition: Come on, Miss Sasako. If he was going to invite someone,he should've invited me instead of Polar Bear.

73.speaker: PENGUIN
73.definition: Of course I did. Argh! I bet everyone is having tons of fun right about now!

74.speaker: PENGUIN
74.character: 笹子さん カフェモカおかわり
74.definition: Could I get another café mocha, Miss Sasako? Yes. So you're all friends from college?

76.speaker: GIRL
76.character: そうそう　動物園にカピバラいますか？
76.definition: Oh, do you have any capybaras at your zoo?

77.speaker: GIRL
77.character: 今　流行ってますよね

78.speaker: GIRL
78.character: カピバラはネズミだってホントですか？
78.definition: Is a capybara really a rodent?

79.speaker: GIRL
79.character: じゃあ　動物園にはカピバラの温泉とか あるんですか？
79.definition: Then is there a capybara hot spring at the zoo? You should use your voice to answer, you know.

80.speaker: KIRINO
80.character: っていうか　さっきから何も　しゃべって ないじゃないですか
80.definition: Not to mention you haven't said a word for a while now.

82.speaker: KIRINO
82.character: 何か用事あるんですか？

83.speaker: HANDA
83.character: いや　風呂の掃除があるから
83.definition: I have to clean the bathroom.

84.speaker: KIRINO
84.character: わぁ～　ちょっと半田さん！

85.speaker: KIRINO
85.character: 風呂の掃除で帰るとか
85.definition: You totally can't say something like that in front of girls!

86.speaker: GIRL
86.definition: Is something wrong? E-Everything is fine. Sorry, he's a little drunk.

87.speaker: GIRL
87.character: 掃除がどうかしたんですか？
87.definition: Did he say something about cleaning {\i1}(souji){\i0}?

88.speaker: KIRINO
88.character: ソ…　ソーセージ注文しようかって 先輩が
88.definition: H-He said we should order some sausage {\i1}(so-se-ji){\i0}!

89.speaker: KIRINO
89.character: ねっ　先輩　僕注文しますね
89.definition: Right? I'll order some right now.

90.speaker: POLAR BEAR
90.character: ソーセージ盛り合わせ２つ

91.speaker: POLAR BEAR
91.character: お刺身　盛り合わせも

92.speaker: KIRINO
92.character: シロクマさん　すみません

93.speaker: KIRINO
93.character: あれ？　パンダくんは？

96.character: わざわざ取りに行ったの？
96.definition: You actually went to get some?

97.speaker: PANDA
97.character: だって　ここ　何もないんだもん
97.definition: Yeah, because they don't have anything here.

98.speaker: KIRINO
98.character: あるでしょ　いろいろ！

99.speaker: KIRINO
99.character: ナッツとか小エビの唐揚げとか
99.definition: See, like nuts and fried shrimp!

102.speaker: GIRL
102.character: パンダが竹食べてるとこ初めて見た！
102.definition: I've never seen a panda eat bamboo before!

104.speaker: GIRL
104.character: 写メ　撮っていいですか？

106.speaker: KIRINO
106.character: 持ち込みはダメだって書いてあるよ
106.definition: It says right here you can't bring outside food or drink.

109.speaker: LADY
109.definition: Here you go... Over here, over here!

110.speaker: KIRINO
110.character: すみません　持ち込みはダメだって 言ったんですけど
110.definition: I'm sorry, I told him he can't bring that in here.

111.speaker: LADY
111.definition: So... So cute! Can I take a picture, too?

112.speaker: KIRINO
112.definition: Um... what about not bringing in outside...

113.speaker: LADY
113.character: いいです　いいです！

114.speaker: GIRL
114.character: 半田さんは何の動物の飼育を しているんですか？
114.definition: What animal do you take care of, Mr. Handa? P-Pandas.

115.speaker: GIRLS
115.character: パンダ！？ パンダの飼育をしてるんですか？
115.definition: Pandas?! You take care of pandas?!

119.speaker: GIRL
119.character: パンダの話 いろいろ　聞かせてください！
119.definition: Tell us more about the pandas!

121.speaker: GIRLS
121.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

123.speaker: GIRLS
123.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

124.speaker: HANDA
124.character: ダラダラしているところ

125.speaker: GIRLS
125.character: キャーッ！　かわいい！！

126.speaker: GIRL
126.character: よく　見分けがつきますね
126.definition: I'm surprised you can tell them all apart.

129.speaker: GIRL
129.character: もっと聞かせてください！

130.speaker: HANDA
130.character: パンダは腸が短くて　竹からだと あまり栄養がとれないんです
130.definition: Pandas have short intestines and can't get much nutrition from bamboo.

131.speaker: HANDA
131.character: だから量で補うために１日中竹を食べているんです
131.definition: That's why they're eating bamboo all day. Wow, their intestines are short!

134.speaker: PANDA
134.character: 半田さん　もっと教えてあげて 僕のかわいいとこ
134.definition: Tell them even more cute things about me, Mr. Handa.

135.speaker: HANDA
135.character: 竹しか食べてないから
135.definition: Since they only eat bamboo, pandas' poop smells good.

136.speaker: HANDA
136.character: ちょっと レモンのにおいに似ているんです

137.speaker: HANDA
137.character: あぁ…　これ　これ

138.speaker: HANDA
138.character: うん　パンダのウンチのにおいです
138.definition: Yes, it smells like panda poop. Here, try it.

139.speaker: KIRINO
139.character: 先輩！　その情報は いらないんじゃないですか？
139.definition: Mr. Handa! I don't think they need that information.

140.speaker: PANDA
140.character: もう！　もっと かわいいエピソードにしてよ
140.definition: Come on, tell them something cuter than that.

141.speaker: HANDA
141.definition: Oh, really? Pandas look cute with their droopy eyes, right?

142.speaker: HANDA
142.character: あれって　実際の目は 小さくて　鋭いんですよ
142.definition: In actuality, their actual eye is small and very sharp. They don't need to know that either.

143.speaker: HANDA
143.definition: Really? I think that's really cute.

145.speaker: SASAKO
145.character: ペンギンさん　カフェモカ　おかわり お待たせしました
145.definition: Mr. Penguin, here you go, your refill on the café mocha.

147.speaker: GIRL
147.character: 今度　パンダコーナー 遊びにいってもいいですか？
147.definition: Is it okay if we come by the panda corner sometime?

148.speaker: HANDA
148.character: もちろんです　見にきてください
148.definition: Of course. Please come. I'll introduce you to Mr. Full-time Panda, too.

149.speaker: GIRL
149.character: 常勤パンダさん？ このパンダさんは何なんですか？
149.definition: Mr. Full-time Panda? So what's this panda, then?

150.speaker: HANDA
150.definition: He's a part-time panda that works two days a week.

151.speaker: GIRL
151.character: へぇ～　アルバイトなんだ？

158.speaker: PENGUIN
158.character: どうも　こんばんは

160.speaker: PANDA
160.character: 忙しいんじゃなかったの？ ペンギンさん

164.speaker: PENGUIN
164.definition: Ma-Ma-halo! Yay! Yay! Yay! Yay! Mr. Penguin, could I have the mic now?

165.speaker: PENGUIN
165.definition: I'm singing one more song! One more song!

168.speaker: KIRINO
168.definition: He's asleep! Wake up, Panda. Wake up!

171.speaker: GIRL
171.character: ねぇ　なんか似てない？

172.speaker: PENGUIN
172.character: このカフェにたどり着いた ラッキーボーイズ　アンド　ガールズ
172.definition: You lucky boys and girls who found this café

173.speaker: GIRL
173.character: 今日は　ありがとうございました
173.definition: Thank you very much for today.

174.speaker: GIRL
174.definition: It was a lot of fun!

175.speaker: GIRL
175.character: また　パンダの話聞かせてください
175.definition: Tell us more about pandas next time! Sure. Please visit the zoo.

176.speaker: GIRLS
176.character: はい じゃあ　おやすみなさい

177.speaker: HANDA
177.character: それじゃ　俺も 風呂の掃除あるから　帰るわ
177.definition: Okay, I have to go clean my bathroom, so I'm heading off.

181.speaker: POLAR BEAR
181.character: うちで　コーヒーでも飲んでく？
181.definition: Did you want to have some coffee at my place?

182.speaker: KIRINO
182.character: はい　シロクマさん

185.speaker: PENGUIN
185.character: あっ！　あれ？　みんなは？
